The terms ‘higher’ and ‘below’ are employed to describe a system of intellectual and political power that offers salvation to transcendent beings or, in rarefied form, serves as a banner to all humans. The original ideas of Apollonian and Dionysian, rather than distinct drives, are thought of as moments within the overall creative and destructive cycle of Dionysus. Growth, and growth in the expression and feeling of power, is the goal or endpoint of all creativity.

